  "text": "Alginate hydrogels are formed by intermolecular ionic crosslinking of G-blocks, with some contributions from MG-blocks [CITATION_1] , by certain divalent cations (e.g. Ca 2+ , Ba 2+ and Sr 2+ ). The structure therefore affects the gel forming ability and the mechanical properties of the gels [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
